Thursday has been declared as a national holiday in Uganda as citizens take to the polls for the country s national elections. Kizza Besigye of opposition party, Forum for Democratic Change (FDC) , has been listed as current President Yoweri Museveni s biggest rival. But Museveni, who has been president for the last 30 years, is still expected to win. MBALI ZWANE and STUART LEWIS spoke to Tendai Marima about the elections . &nbsp;All images: Tendai Marima